"Local IPs are read from the system network interfaces.\n\nVPN is detected by the presence of utun, ppp, or ipsec interfaces.\n\nPublic IP is fetched from api.ipify.org over HTTPS. Only your outbound request is sent — no other data. Refreshed every 5 minutes.\n\nConnectivity check is an HTTPS HEAD request to Apple's captive portal endpoint (captive.apple.com). This respects your system proxy settings. True ICMP ping requires root on macOS, so this is used instead." = "Local IPs are read from the system network interfaces.\n\nVPN is detected by the presence of utun, ppp, or ipsec interfaces.\n\nPublic IP is fetched from api.ipify.org over HTTPS. Only your outbound request is sent — no other data. Refreshed every 5 minutes.\n\nConnectivity check is an HTTPS HEAD request to Apple's captive portal endpoint (captive.apple.com). This respects your system proxy settings. True ICMP ping requires root on macOS, so this is used instead.";
